<br>
I don't believe there is any surprise here.  Sure, many of us still have patience.  But one of the things that helps to maintain that patience is the unloading of emotional dead weight.  This board is where all the waste products will appear.  <br>
<br>
You can't tell me that as heavy gamers, we haven't played a game on a major commerical video gaming system and shouted at the screen, yelled about the calls, hit walls, threw things, etc.  This board is where that energy can be unloaded in a public setting with other people who feel the same way.  I don't see the problem with that.  And if any get inappropraite or overboard, at least we have overseers who can remove them.  You can't remove the hole in your wall quite as easily.<br>
<br>
